{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_89","type":"agent_message","text":"The missing directory now makes sense: `accessors-smart` defines classes on a parent built-in class loader, and the agent only auto-extracts classes loaded by non-built-in/custom loaders. That means the last viable path is to synthesize the predefined-classes payload ourselves from the deterministic test-generated bytecode, using GraalVM’s expected hash-and-bytecode layout."}}
